author: Brian
title: The NFL reveals its MVP, Rookie of the Year and other 2016 award winners
text:
Feb 4, 2017 at 8:43p ET 0Shares And the winner is ... 
The NFL is handing out its 2016 awards at the NFL Honors show tonight on FOX, and we're revealing the winners live! 
We'll continue to update with the winners as they're announced, so keep checking back to find out who took home the MVP, Rookie of the Year, Coach of the Year and more. 
And be sure to tune in to FOX for Sunday's Super Bowl between the Atlanta Falcons and New England Patriots (6:30 p.m. ET). Defensive Player of the Year: Khalil Mack, Raiders 
2016 stats: 73 tackles, 11 sacks, 1 INT Offensive Rookie of the Year: Dak Prescott, Cowboys 
2016 stats: 67.8% completions, 3,667 yards, 23-4 TD/INT, 104.9 passer rating Coach of the Year: Jason Garrett, Cowboys 
2016 coaching record : 13-4 Defensive Rookie of the Year: Joey Bosa, Chargers 
2016 stats : 41 tackles, 10.5 sacks Getty Images Getty Images Offensive Player of the Year: Matt Ryan, Falcons 
Jason Getz USA TODAY Sports
